corresponding mean level of 2.3 mm after 5 years of function. Regarding clinical 
complications, a different pattern, mainly related to the type of prosthetic 
construction used, was observed between the groups. The number of visits clearly 
indicated that severely resorbed jaws provided with overdentures were the most 
demanding.

