BACKGROUND: Few risk functions for the prediction of coronary heart disease 
mortality have been produced in Italy. This study used a large population sample 
to evaluate the effect of major risk factors on coronary mortality.
METHODS: Coronary deaths in 45 cohorts of men (n = 31317, aged 30-69 years) were 
studied and related to selected cardiovascular risk factors.
RESULTS: After 6 years, 1089 men had died, of whom 239 were coronary fatalities. 
