analysis of MRFIT primary screenees in the USA to facilitate valid comparison. 
The coefficients in the present study were similar to those in the US cohort: no 
statistically significant differences could be detected when comparing the pairs 
of coefficients.
CONCLUSION: Coefficients relating cholesterol, blood pressure and cigarette 
smoking to coronary mortality in Italian men are similar to those in American 
men from the same age groups.

