Potential years of life lost: what is the denominator?

Marlow AK(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Public Health Medicine, Powys Health, The Laurels, Bronllys, 
Brecon.

OBJECTIVE: To suggest an appropriate denominator for use with the statistic 
"potential years of life lost", in order to facilitate valid comparisons between 
health authorities.
DESIGN: Analysis of OPCS population and mortality data for the period 1987-91.
SETTING: Data for Wales were analysed to provide comparisons between the nine 
district health authorities.
SUBJECTS: There were 46,139 males and 30,258 females--that is, all deaths of 
Welsh residents, aged under 75 years, during the period 1987-91.
